# 📘 Execution of HDFS Commands in Hadoop

## 🧑‍💻 Experiment Title

Execution of HDFS Commands for Interaction with Hadoop Environment

---

## 🎯 Objective

To perform and understand various Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS) commands for file and directory management within a Hadoop environment.

---

## 🛠️ Requirements

* Ubuntu/Linux System
* Hadoop Installed (Single Node Setup)
* Java Installed
* Terminal Access

---

## ▶️ Procedure

### Step 1: Start Hadoop HDFS Services

```bash
start-dfs.sh
```

### Step 2: Verify Services

```bash
jps
```

---

## 📂 HDFS Commands Executed

### 1. List Root Directory

```bash
hdfs dfs -ls /
```

### 2. Create Directory

```bash
hdfs dfs -mkdir /user/pradeep
```

### 3. Create Nested Directory

```bash
hdfs dfs -mkdir -p /user/pradeep/data/input
```

### 4. Upload File to HDFS

```bash
hdfs dfs -put sample.txt /user/pradeep/data/input
```

### 5. List Files in Directory

```bash
hdfs dfs -ls /user/pradeep/data/input
```

### 6. Display File Content

```bash
hdfs dfs -cat /user/pradeep/data/input/sample.txt
```

### 7. Download File from HDFS

```bash
hdfs dfs -get /user/pradeep/data/input/sample.txt /home/hadoop/
```

### 8. Copy File in HDFS

```bash
hdfs dfs -cp /user/pradeep/data/input/sample.txt /user/pradeep/data/sample_copy.txt
```

### 9. Rename/Move File

```bash
hdfs dfs -mv /user/pradeep/data/sample_copy.txt /user/pradeep/data/sample_renamed.txt
```

### 10. Check Disk Usage

```bash
hdfs dfs -du /user/pradeep
```

### 11. Set Replication Factor

```bash
hdfs dfs -setrep -w 2 /user/pradeep/data/input/sample.txt
```

### 12. Delete File

```bash
hdfs dfs -rm /user/pradeep/data/input/sample.txt
```

### 13. Delete Directory

```bash
hdfs dfs -rm -r /user/pradeep/data
```

